xubuntu-default-settings (16.10.3) yakkety; urgency=medium

  * debian/control:
    - Drop dependencies on dbus-user-session and systemd, these
      are not needed with the previous changes and seem to be related
      to slowness with adjusting display backlights.

 -- Sean Davis <smd.seandavis@gmail.com>  Thu, 06 Oct 2016 20:04:33 -0400

xubuntu-default-settings (16.10.2) yakkety; urgency=medium

  * Revert systemd user unit changes (LP: #1622303)
  * usr/share/xsessions/xubuntu.desktop: Switch Exec= line back to
    direct startxfce4 execution.

 -- Sean Davis <smd.seandavis@gmail.com>  Wed, 28 Sep 2016 06:02:49 -0400

xubuntu-default-settings (16.10.1) yakkety; urgency=medium

  * Add xubuntu-session.target user systemd unit.
  * usr/share/xsessions/xubuntu.desktop: Switch Exec= line from direct
    startxfce4 execution to running xubuntu-session.target through systemd.
    Bump xfce4-session dependency accordingly.
  * Add a Breaks: for the upstart versions that don't yet have the necessary
    Xsession.d fixes for systemd user sessions yet.
  * Depend on dbus-user-session and the systemd version that provides
    graphical-session.target.

 -- Martin Pitt <martin.pitt@ubuntu.com>  Sun, 31 Jul 2016 12:00:45 +0200

